For Task 3, I explored both coding practice platforms and cloud-based collaboration tools. For the coding practice component, I used HackerRank and completed a beginner-level problem titled “Solve Me First.” This helped me understand how to write, run, and submit code on an online platform. It also gave me a basic introduction to problem-solving in a structured environment.

For the collaboration component, I created a Google Form titled “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” consisting of five questions. The form included a mix of multiple-choice and short-answer questions to test basic knowledge of digital literacy among students. I also linked the form responses to a Google Sheet, which allows easy collection and analysis of responses.

This task helped me understand how coding platforms can be used to improve programming skills, while tools like Google Forms can be used for data collection, surveys, and academic collaboration. These tools will be useful in my academic journey for assignments, projects, and skill development.
